# EduPath: API Documentation & Entity-Relationship (ER) Diagrams

This document outlines the database schema (via ER Diagrams) and lists the core REST API endpoints of the EduPath Online Education Platform.

---

## 1. Entity-Relationship (ER) Diagram

Below is the database relationship diagram of the system modeled using Mermaid.js syntax:

```mermaid
erDiagram
    USER {
        int id PK
        string username
        string email
        string role "STUDENT | MENTOR | ADMIN"
        bool is_email_verified
        bool profile_complete
    }
    
    PROFILE {
        int id PK
        int user_id FK
        string title
        string skills
        int years_of_experience
        string location
        string education_level
        bool is_approved
        bool is_suspended
        image avatar
    }

    COURSE {
        int id PK
        string title
        string slug
        string description
        int mentor_id FK
        decimal price
        string level "BEGINNER | INTERMEDIATE | ADVANCED"
        string category
        bool is_approved
        bool is_published
        decimal rating_average
        int total_reviews
    }

    MODULE {
        int id PK
        int course_id FK
        string title
        int order
    }

    LESSON {
        int id PK
        int module_id FK
        string title
        string content_type "VIDEO | PDF | DOCUMENT"
        string video_url
        file file_attachment
        string body_text
        int order
    }

    QUIZ_QUESTION {
        int id PK
        int lesson_id FK
        string question_text
        string question_type "SINGLE_CHOICE | MULTIPLE_CHOICE | FILL_BLANK"
        int points
        int order
    }

    QUIZ_OPTION {
        int id PK
        int question_id FK
        string text
        bool is_correct
        int order
    }

    ENROLLMENT {
        int id PK
        int student_id FK
        int course_id FK
        datetime enrolled_at
        bool is_active
        decimal progress_percent
    }

    PAYMENT {
        int id PK
        int enrollment_id FK
        string gateway "STRIPE | PAYPAL"
        string status "PENDING | COMPLETED | FAILED | REFUNDED"
        decimal amount
        string transaction_id
    }

    CERTIFICATE {
        int id PK
        int enrollment_id FK
        int student_id FK
        datetime issued_at
        string verification_uuid
    }

    QUIZ_ATTEMPT {
        int id PK
        int student_id FK
        int lesson_id FK
        int attempt_number
        decimal score_achieved
        bool is_submitted
        datetime started_at
    }

    REVIEW {
        int id PK
        int course_id FK
        int student_id FK
        int rating
        string comment
        bool is_flagged
    }

    REVIEW_REPORT {
        int id PK
        int review_id FK
        int reported_by_id FK
        string reason
        string status "PENDING | DISMISSED | REVIEWED"
    }

    USER ||--|| PROFILE : "has"
    USER ||--o{ COURSE : "mentors"
    USER ||--o{ ENROLLMENT : "registers"
    COURSE ||--o{ MODULE : "contains"
    MODULE ||--o{ LESSON : "contains"
    LESSON ||--o{ QUIZ_QUESTION : "has_questions"
    QUIZ_QUESTION ||--o{ QUIZ_OPTION : "has_options"
    COURSE ||--o{ ENROLLMENT : "enrolls"
    ENROLLMENT ||--|| CERTIFICATE : "rewards"
    ENROLLMENT ||--o{ PAYMENT : "bills"
    USER ||--o{ QUIZ_ATTEMPT : "takes"
    LESSON ||--o{ QUIZ_ATTEMPT : "evaluated_by"
    USER ||--o{ REVIEW : "writes"
    COURSE ||--o{ REVIEW : "reviewed_by"
    REVIEW ||--o{ REVIEW_REPORT : "flagged_by"
```

